There's no "La" in the stage name of Ilona Staller. "La" is the definite article used for single female beings or single female things in Italian, it means "the". In Italian, «il/lo/l'», «i/gli», «la/l'», «le» all means "the", but with different declensions (male singular, male plural, female singular, female plural). The stage name of Ilona Staller was invented by italian porn movie producer Riccardo Schicchi.
